<h2>Portland Christian Center's Easter Sunday for Kids is WAY better than an Easter Egg Hunt!</h2><div id="sermon-info" class="sermon"><ul class="sermon-buttons"></ul><!-- .sermon-buttons --><p class="sermon-meta">Posted Mar 12th, 2013 &nbsp;  </p></div><!-- .sermon --><div id="text"><h3>Easter Sunday for kids is WAY better than an Easter egg hunt ...</h3>
<p><i>At Portland Christian Center, we make children our top priority and that includes ensuring that they have a blast at our Easter Kids Church on Sunday, March 31! They will have tons of fun learning about the meaning of Easter through object lessons, bible stories, live music, treats, games, puppets, and prizes. Read all about our amazing weekly children's church event below ...&nbsp;</i></p>
<h4>Adventure Kids' Church Easter Details</h4>
<p><strong>Sunday, March 31, during our adult Easter services <br />[ <a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/easter/">more info about adult services</a> ]</strong></p>
<p>All Easter Activities for kids will be in the Trailhead and Gymnasium located on the first floor of our building at 5700 SW Dosch Road, Portland, OR 97239.&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>First Session</strong> : 9:00 AM - 10:30 AM<br /><strong>Second Session</strong> : 10:45 AM - 12:00 PM</p>
<p>Check in for Kid's&nbsp;Easter Activities begins 10 to 15 minutes before the start of church on Easter Sunday. All volunteers have been through training and background checks to assure the safey of our children during children's church activities this Easter Sunday.</p>
<p><strong>How To Check In Your Child</strong></p>
<p>Preschool and Elementary Kids both check-in at our secure check-in locations. We have three check in locations: upstairs by the main entrance, downstairs by the gym entrance, and downstairs at our Adventure Kids Church room. Children who are three years old or younger check in upstairs in our Professional Nursery. If you need directions, we will have greeters at every entrance that would be happy to direct you to the best check-in location for you.&nbsp;<strong>[ <a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/ministries/children/">more info about check in and security</a> ]&nbsp;</strong></p>
<h4>A &nbsp;Free Family Easter Activity in Portland, Oregon</h4>
<p>We are proud of Easter Sunday at Portland Christian Center. Pastor Phillip Hahn and his team of adult and kid volunteers have been preparing for weeks. You won't want your kids to miss out on all of our Easter themed activities, including a <strong>kid's size cave</strong> that your kids can explore! Below we have listed some of the other activities happening during our Easter Kids' Church.&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>The <strong>Easter Story</strong> told through object lessons, imagery, live drama, and more!</li>
<li>A p<strong>uppet show featuring Speck</strong> and his friend, Pastor Phil. Together they will unravel Speck's confusion about what goes in an Easter basket! Your kids will be rolling on the floor with laughter over the item's Speck thinks should go in an Easter basket.</li>
<li>Pastor Phil loves to throw in <strong>an illusion or two</strong>. Do you have a budding young magician? Check out Pastor Phil's expectional skill at "slight of hand" during our Sunday morning kids church.&nbsp;</li>
<li>Each week our adult and kid led worship team leads our Adventure Kids' Church in worship. Expect another week of great <strong>live music</strong> this Easter Sunday.</li>
<li><strong>Every kid gets a prize!</strong> What more could any kid ask for? In addition to the free bible bucks they get this week, kids can earn Bible Bucks each week at our Kids Church and redeem them from "The Store". Kids also have the opportunity to give and provide for a hungry kid somewhere in the world.&nbsp;</li>
<li><strong>Yummy snacks in between sessions</strong>. Kids are welcome to eat a donut, drink chocolate milk or juice in between the first and second Kids Church sessions. If mom or dad would rather they not have a treat, no problem, just let us know.</li>
</ul>
<h3>What About Other Kids' Activities?</h3>
<p><i>Portland Christian Center's children's pastor Phil Hahn is serious about making sure that kids are engaged in <strong>meaningful learning about God</strong> during each of our Adventure Kids activities, classes and groups, and we have a lot of options! If you are looking for a place for you or for you and your child to grow in God, to learn moral principles and to belong, then we invite you to visit us on a Sunday morning or Wednesday night. We welcome you as our guest to experience the love and family of Portland Christian Center. </i><strong>[ <a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/ministries/children/">more info about Adventure Kids</a> ] [<a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/ministries/adult-education/different-children-different-needs/"> parenting classes </a>]</strong></p>
